13 4.1-03-01. Definitions.
14 As used in this chapter:
15 1. "Beef producer" means any person that has an ownership interest in cattle.
16 2. "Cattle" means live domesticated bovine animals.
17 3. "Cattle feeder" means a person in the business of feeding cattle for the purpose of
18 adding weight to the cattle prior to slaughter.
19 4. "Cattle industry representative" means an individual who is or has been a beef
20 producer, cattle feeder, dairy producer, or representative of a public livestock market in
21 the state.
22 5. "Commission" means the North Dakota beef commission.
