1 SECTION 6. AMENDMENT. Section 4.1-03-17 of the North Dakota Century Code is
2 amended and reenacted as follows:
3 4.1-03-17. Permitted refunds of assessment - Refunds requiring certification by
4 attorney general.
5 1. a.When the attorney general certifies to the commission that refunds of assessments
6 paid under subdivision a of subsection 1 of section 4.1-03-11 are no longer precluded
7 by federal law, the commission may provide to producers refunds of assessments paid
8 under subdivision a of subsection 1 of section 4.1-03-11.
9 b. Refunds of assessments paid under subdivision b of subsection 1 of section
10 4.1-03-11 are available, subject to the requirements of this section.
11 2. a. To receive a permitted refund of any assessment paid in accordance with this
12 chapter, a producer shall request a refund application from the commission within
13 sixty days after the date of the sale. The request may be made orally, in writing,
14 or in electronic form.
15 b. The producer must complete the refund application and return the application to
16 the commission, together with a record of the assessment paid, within ninety
17 days after the date of the sale. The application may be returned to the
18 commission in person, by mail, or in electronic form. The commission shall then
19 refund the net amount of the assessment that had been collected.
20 c. If a request for a refund is not submitted to the commission within the prescribed
21 time period, the producer is presumed to have agreed to the assessment.
