11 redistricting plan to amend district boundaries, provided each district contains at least
12 three undivided counties. If two - thirds of the elected commission members vote in
13 favor of the proposed redistricting plan, the commission shall adopt the plan. If the
14 commission adopts a redistricting plan, the commission shall submit a bill to the next
15 legislative assembly to amend subsection 1 in a manner consistent with the results o f
16 the redistricting plan. The redistricting plan becomes effective on the date the
17 amended district boundaries under subsection 1 become effective .
18 SECTION 8. A new section to chapter 4.1-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
19 and enacted as follows:
20 Director of the North Dakota state university extension service - Nomination and
21 election of district commission candidates.
22 1. a. The director of the North Dakota state university extension service shall oversee
23 district representative commission member nominations and elections.
24 b. Between October first and December thirty-first of each year, the director shall
25 conduct the nominating and election process to elect successors for districts with
26 terms expiring that fiscal year.
27 c. The director shall notify all known cattle industry representatives in the respective
28 district and request nominations for district representative commission candidates
29 no fewer than forty-five nor more than sixty days before the district representative
30 commission election. The notice must be published in all official county
31 newspapers within the district or by reliable electronic means.
