1 d. To be eligible as a candidate in a district commission election, at least five cattle
2 industry representatives who reside in the district shall nominate the candidate in
3 writing. A cattle industry representative may not self-nominate.
4 e. Upon receiving the district commission nominations, the director shall certify that
5 nominated candidates meet the requirements of section 4.1 - 03 - 02. The director
6 shall prepare the election ballots with the names of the certified nominated district
7 commission candidates. Each ballot also must include a statement indicating:
8 (1) The date, time, and location the director will open the ballots and tabulate
9 the results;
10 (2) The last date by which the ballots must be postmarked or filed with the
11 director; and
12 (3) Any cattle industry representative in the district may be present at the time
13 the ballots are opened and tabulated.
14 f. The director shall hold the district commission election by mail paper ballot. The
15 director shall mail the ballots to each known cattle industry representative in the
16 district at least thirty days before the election.
17 g. The director shall canvass the votes. The director shall notify the commission and
18 the governor that the election has taken place, and provide to the commission
19 and the governor the name and address and term of the newly elected district
20 representative commission member.
21 2. If the cattle industry representatives in a district fail to elect an individual, as required
22 by this section, the director shall notify the commission and the governor. The
23 governor shall appoint a cattle industry representative who meets the requirements of
24 section 4.1 - 03 - 02 to serve as the district commission member for the district. An
25 individual appointed under this subsection has the same rights, duties, and privileges
26 as an elected commission member.
27 3. Each eligible voter is entitled to one vote and must vote in the district in which the
28 voter's livestock operation headquarters is located. If an eligible voter has multiple
29 livestock operation headquarters in more than one district, the eligible voter shall cast
30 their vote in the district in which the voter physically resides.
