13 SECTION 10. A new section to chapter 4.1-03 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
14 and enacted as follows:
15 Referendums - Assessments.
16 1. If petitioned by at least fifteen percent of the cattle industry representatives of the
17 state, the commission shall conduct a referendum among the cattle industry
18 representatives to determine the amount by which the assessment imposed under
19 section 4.1 - 03 - 11 should be adjusted .
20 2. No more than fifty percent of the cattle industry representatives who signed the
21 petition may reside in the same district.
22 3. The commission shall hold an assessment referendum by mail paper ballot. The
23 commission shall prepare the ballots with the petitioned amount by which the
24 assessment imposed under section 4.1 - 03 - 11 is proposed to be adjusted and
25 distribute the ballots to each cattle industry representative at least thirty days before
26 the last date for filing ballots.
27 4. Each ballot must include a statement indicating:
28 a. The date the petition was filed and the number of signatures on the petition;
29 b. The date, time, and location the commission will open the ballots and tabulate the
30 results;
